1. Create a model

1.a Create Ecore
Namespace = namespace in XSD

1.b Create Types
1.b.1 Definition
SuperType contains CDKProvides or CDKConsumes (need to load CDK ecore before)
Type has annotation:
- source: http:///org/eclipse/emf/ecore/util/ExtendedMetaData
- key: name
- value: [blank]
1.b.2 Contents
Create fields following XSD
Attributes and children must have "Derived" set to true.
Use annotations, source http:///org/eclipse/emf/ecore/util/ExtendedMetaData
- group: #group:0 (EFeatureMap container, the "any" element)
- kind: element
- namespace: ##targetNamespace (namespace of package)
if not same in ecore and XSD - name: [name in XSD]
For enum: Create enum, put in "Literal" the String as in XSD

1.c Generate code

Create a new EMF Generator Model for this Ecore. Add references to jbi.genmodel and cdk.genmodel.
Only generate genmodel for your component.
In genmodel:
* Select top-level element:
- All > Copyright
- Model > Model Directory: .../src-model
* Select package:
- set basePackage to pluginId 
* In build.properties
- add src-model to src folders
- add model folder to binary build

1.d Finish

* Add dependency to CDK plugin.
* In plugin.xml:
- Ensure package is registered in EMF (org.eclipse.emf.ecore.generated_package)
- add a jbiExtensionPackage, set URI as the namespace of your component.

